                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3920</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCAR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Britannic Majesty’s
                    Chargé d’Affaires and has the honor to state that, for the reasons given in the
                    Department’s memoranda of January 25 and February 6 [<hi rend="italic">8</hi>],
                    1919, the Government of the United States seriously questions the advisability
                    of assisting at this time the return to China of Chinese workmen and coolies who
                    have been under the influence of the Bolshevik rule in Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
